cs.DB, cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.AI. 

The paper discusses a platform for visualizing patterns and trends in large datasets, which falls under the category of data management and analysis. Therefore, cs.DB is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the user interface and user study, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of a visual query language and optimization techniques suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and systems and infrastructure (cs.SI). Finally, the use of machine learning and data science techniques suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
